```
class CalculatorPresenter {
    constructor(model, view) {
        this.model = model;
        this.view = view;
    }

    onAddClicked(num1, num2) {
        this.performCalculation(this.model.add.bind(this.model), num1, num2);
    }

    onSubtractClicked(num1, num2) {
        this.performCalculation(this.model.subtract.bind(this.model), num1, num2);
    }

    onMultiplyClicked(num1, num2) {
        this.performCalculation(this.model.multiply.bind(this.model), num1, num2);
    }

    onDivideClicked(num1, num2) {
        this.performCalculation(this.model.divide.bind(this.model), num1, num2);
    }

    performCalculation(op, num1, num2) {
        try {
            op(num1, num2);
            this.view.updateResult(this.model.result);
        } catch (error) {
            this.view.showError(error);
        }
    }
}
```

In this example, the Model is represented by the CalculatorModel class, which performs the calculations and stores the result in a property. The View is represented by the CalculatorView class, which handles the user interface and user inputs. The Presenter is represented by the CalculatorPresenter class, which mediates between the Model and the View.

The View listens to the user actions and sends them to the Presenter, which then interacts with the Model to perform the calculation. The result is then sent back to the View for display. If there is an error, the Presenter sends the error message to the View for display.

